## 2. Authentication System

### 2.1 Do Alag Login Systems
- **Owner/Admin Login** — alag login page/flow
- **Reseller Login** — alag login page/flow

### 2.2 Owner Account Creation
- Owner ka account **source code se hi create hota hai** (seed script / `.env` config / initial setup script) — koi public signup nahi.
- Owner login ke baad hi **Admin accounts** create kar sakta hai.

### 2.3 Login Fields
- **Owner/Admin:** Username/Identity + Password + **Security PIN**
- **Reseller:** Username + Password

### 2.4 Two-Factor Authentication (2FA / Authenticator)
- Har role (Owner, Admin, Reseller) ke liye optional/mandatory **TOTP-based Authenticator** support (Google Authenticator / Authy compatible).
- Jab koi user **first time login** kare, system usse authenticator app se QR code scan karke connect karne ko bole.
- Ek baar connect hone ke baad, **har login attempt par authenticator code mandatory** hoga.

---

## 3. Roles & Permissions

### 3.1 Owner (Highest Access)
- Sab kuch jo Admin kar sakta hai + extra:
  - Sabhi **Resellers ko search** kar sakta hai (by name/username)
  - **Admin accounts create** kar sakta hai
  - Kisi bhi Reseller ko **infinite credits** de sakta hai (Reseller khud ko infinite nahi de sakta)
  - Full system-wide visibility (sab resellers, sab keys, sab logs)

### 3.2 Admin
- Owner jaisa hi almost powerful — bas Owner-only cheezein (jaise Admin create karna) nahi kar sakta.
- Reseller create/manage kar sakta hai
- Sab packages create/manage kar sakta hai
- Global user/key management

### 3.3 Reseller
- Apne khud ke credits ke andar rehke keys generate karna
- Apne assigned packages dekhna aur unke through keys banana
- Apne banaye hue users (keys) ko manage karna: ban, pause, unban, unpause, delete, HWID reset
- Agar permission mile to:
  - Naya Reseller create kar sakta hai (sub-reseller)
  - API/Bot access use kar sakta hai

---

## 4. Credits System

- Har Reseller ke paas ek **Credit Balance** hota hai.
- **1 Credit = 1 Key generate karne ka right** (jitni keys utne credits deduct honge).
- Owner/Admin reseller create karte waqt usse initial credits assign karega.
- **Reseller ko max ek baar me 10,000 credits** diye ja sakte hain (limit).
- **Owner apne aap ko ya kisi Reseller ko infinite credits** de sakta hai — ye option sirf Owner ke paas hoga, Reseller ke paas nahi.
- Reseller apna khud ka credit **kisi aur ko nahi de sakta / khud add nahi kar sakta**.

### Credit Dashboard (Reseller ke Overview tab me dikhna chahiye):
- Total Credits
- Used Credits
- Remaining Credits
- **Last 10 Keys ka history** (kab bani, kis package ki, kitne din ki)

---

## 5. Key Management

Key generate karte waqt niche diye options honge:

| Field | Description |
|---|---|
| Key Name | Custom naam de sakte hain key ko |
| Expiry (Days) | Kitne din ki key honi chahiye — **max limit: 2012 days** |
| HWID Lock | Toggle option — ON hone par pehli login ke baad HWID lock ho jayega |
| HWID Reset Allowed | Agar ye ON hai, to key ke owner (end-user) khud apna HWID reset kar sakta hai (isse ek key multiple devices par use ho sakti hai agar allow kiya gaya ho — is wajah se generally isse *off* rakha jata hai jab tak zaroori na ho) |

> Security Note: HWID reset ka option jitna zyada open rahega, utna zyada chance hoga ki ek hi key multiple logon me share ho. Isliye default OFF rakhna recommended hai; sirf jab support ke liye zaroori ho tabhi manually reset karna better practice hai.

---

## 6. Package Management

- Owner/Admin multiple **Packages** create kar sakte hain (e.g. "Aimkill", "Aimsilent" jaise custom product names — jo bhi aapke software products hain).
- Har package ke andar hi uska **"Create Key"** button hoga — us package ki key sirf usi package ke section se banegi.
- Reseller create karte waqt Owner/Admin **select kar sakta hai ki kaunse packages us reseller ko assign karne hain** (checkbox list — jo packages select honge sirf wahi Reseller ke dashboard me dikhenge).

---

## 7. User Management (End-Users / Keys)

Reseller/Admin/Owner apne banaye hue users (license holders) ko manage kar sakein:

| Action | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Pause | User ki key temporarily disable ho jaye. Button "Pause" → click karne par "Unpause" me badal jaye (toggle) |
| Ban | User permanently block ho jaye. Button "Ban" → click karne par "Unban" me badal jaye (toggle) |
| Delete | User/key permanently remove ho jaye |
| HWID Reset | Us particular user ka HWID clear kar diya jaye taaki wo naye device/IP se login kar sake |

Ye sab actions **Users tab** ke andar se hi available honge, per-user row me buttons ke through.

