## 8. Dashboard UI Structure (Sidebar + Tabs)

Sidebar-based layout, left side me menu, right side me content. Design **minimalist** hoga (see Section 1.1) — clean sidebar, simple icons, tables/cards ke saath subtle borders, extra clutter/decoration avoid karna.

### Tab 1 — Overview
- Credit Balance (Total / Used / Remaining)
- Last 10 Keys history (name, package, created date, expiry)
- **App ID & Secret ID** (isko sirf Owner apne Overview tab me khud dekh sakta hai — Admin ya Reseller ke Overview tab me ye dikhega nahi)

### Tab 2 — Packages
- List of assigned packages (cards/list)
- Har package card ke andar **"Create Key"** button

### Tab 3 — Users
- Table of all generated keys/users
  - Columns: Key/Username, Package, Created Date, Expiry, Status
  - Actions: Pause/Unpause, Ban/Unban, Delete, Reset HWID

### Tab 4 — API / Bot System
- Discord Bot source code / setup instructions is tab se milega
- Agar Reseller ke paas ye access nahi hai to "Upgrade to unlock" type CTA dikhna chahiye
- Agar access hai to:
  - API key generate/regenerate karne ka option
  - Bot setup guide + config file/token input
  - Bot se end-users seedha Discord se hi key generate kar sakein (jaise web dashboard se karte hain)

### (Owner/Admin Extra)
- Reseller Search bar (naam se search)
- "Create Admin" button (Owner only)
- "Create Reseller" form (with credit assign + package assign + sub-reseller permission + API access toggle + App ID/Secret option)
- **Owner-Only Visibility:** Owner apna khud ka App ID/Secret dekh sakta hai, aur saath hi **kisi bhi Reseller ya Admin ka App ID/Secret bhi search karke dekh sakta hai** (Reseller list me row expand karke ya reseller profile page par). Ye visibility sirf Owner role ke liye hai — Admin ya Reseller sirf apna khud ka App ID/Secret dekh sakte hain, doosron ka nahi.

