## 10. Suggested Database Schema (High Level)

- `users` (owner/admin/reseller — role, username, password_hash, security_pin, 2fa_secret, credits, parent_reseller_id, app_id, secret_key, permissions JSON)
  - `app_id` / `secret_key`: har account (Owner/Admin/Reseller) ke paas apna ek App ID + Secret hota hai jo API/Bot authentication ke liye use hota hai. Reseller create karte waqt owner/admin decide karta hai ki naya generate karna hai ya default/existing use karna hai. Visibility rule: sirf Owner role hi kisi bhi account ka `app_id`/`secret_key` query kar sakta hai; baaki roles sirf apna khud ka dekh sakte hain (row-level access control zaroori).
- `packages` (id, name, created_by)
- `reseller_packages` (reseller_id, package_id) — many-to-many mapping
- `keys` (id, key_string, key_name, package_id, created_by_reseller_id, expiry_days, hwid, hwid_reset_allowed, status[active/paused/banned], created_at)
- `credit_logs` (reseller_id, action, amount, timestamp)
- `api_tokens` (reseller_id, token, bot_access_enabled)

